   <pb facs="3"/>
   <head>To his absent Diana.</head>
   <l>SEuer'd from sweete Content, my liues sole light;</l>
   <l>Banisht by ouer-weening wit from my desire:</l>
   <l>This poore acceptance onely I require,</l>
   <l>That though my fault haue forc'd me from thy sight;</l>
   <l>Yet that thou wouldst (my sorrowes to requite)</l>
   <l>Review these Sonnets, pictures of thy praise;</l>
   <l>Wherein each woe thy wondrous worth doth raise,</l>
   <l>Though first thy worth bereft me of delight.</l>
   <l>See them forsaken: for I them forsooke,</l>
   <l>Forsaken first of thee, next of my sence;</l>
   <l>And when thou deignst on their blacke teares to looke,</l>
   <l>Shed not one teare my teares to recompence:</l>
   <l>But ioy in this (though Fates gainst mee repine)</l>
   <l>My verse still liues, to witnes thee diuine.</l>
</div>
